1) Monroe's Motivated Sequence
	A) 5 steps
		I) building credibility
			a) prove credibility
				1) explain competence
			b) prove why it matters
		II) using evidence
			a) statistics/research
			b) be specifiic with it
				1) ideally novel evidence
		III) reasoning
			a) specific instance
				1) draw conclusions from specific things
					A) avoid hasty generalizations
			b) causal reasoning
			c) analogical reasoning
				1) compare similar cases
		IV) appealing to emotions
		V) call to action

2) appealing to emotion
	A) be honest/sincere
		I) make people care about the topic
			a) some topics evoke certain emotions
				1) anger is easy for mine

5) speech example
